## API Reference

### `LayerCard`

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `as` | `keyof HTMLElementTagNameMap` | No | Element to render. Defaults to `"div"`. |
| `children` | `Snippet` | No | Card contents. |
| `class` | `string` | No | Additional classes. |
| `layered` | `boolean` | No | Uses the layered root styles for `LayerCardSecondary` + `LayerCardPrimary` composition. Defaults to `false`. |

LayerCard also accepts standard HTML attributes for the rendered element.

### `LayerCardPrimary`

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `children` | `Snippet` | No | Primary card content. |
| `class` | `string` | No | Additional classes. |

LayerCardPrimary also accepts standard `HTMLDivElement` attributes.

### `LayerCardSecondary`

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `children` | `Snippet` | No | Secondary header content. |
| `class` | `string` | No | Additional classes. |

LayerCardSecondary also accepts standard `HTMLDivElement` attributes.

## Svelte Notes

The Svelte package exports named components (`LayerCardPrimary`, `LayerCardSecondary`) instead of React compound properties (`LayerCard.Primary`, `LayerCard.Secondary`). Use `layered` on the root when composing the primary and secondary regions.
